caption:
This photograph appears to be an aerial view of a landscape at twilight or early evening. The image captures a densely forested area surrounded by a body of water, possibly a lake or coastal sea. The scene is dominated by dark hues, indicating low light conditions, with a slight purple cast that might suggest the photograph was taken at dusk.

There are a few points of interest in the photograph:
1. On the left side, there is a well-lit area which looks like a small settlement or a group of buildings. The lights suggest human habitation or activity.
2. Toward the right of the image, along the edge of the forest, a road or path can be seen curving around the terrain. This road is bordered closely by the water.
3. A strip of land juts into the water from the right, featuring what seems to be a brightly lit facility or structure at its tip, standing out against the dark surroundings.

The natural landscape is mainly coniferous trees, which are common in cooler climates near water bodies. Additionally, the calm water, likely reflecting some light, subtly highlights the outline of the land.

Overall, the photograph conveys a serene yet somewhat remote or secluded setting, characterized by its natural beauty and minimal human alteration.
title: Aerial view looking southwest near U.S. Navy installations. Facilities will be built in the areas for a Trident submarine base, which will increase the population and affect the life of both humans and animals living there. The photo shows Bangor Annex Devils Hole, a diked estuary converted to a freshwater lake and the small boat waterfront facility.
